article.description: Cornell finishes with 10 straight points, beats Brown 57-49
article.headline: Cornell finishes with 10 straight points, beats Brown 57-49
article.linkText: Cornell finishes with 10 straight points, beats Brown 57-49
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Galal Cancer had 11 points, six rebounds and four assists on Friday night, and Cornell scored the last 10 points to beat Brown 57-49. Devin Cherry added 11 points and David Onuorah had seven blocks, tying for third on the Big Red's single-game list. Cancer had the only field goal by either team in the final three minutes and Cornell was 8 of 10 from the foul line during that span. Cornell (10-9, 2-1 Ivy) held its fourth straight opponent under 50 points. Brown (9-11, 0-3) had 49 points and a two-point lead on Cedric Kuakumensah's free throw with 3:31 left. The Bears went scoreless with 0-of-6 shooting the rest of the way. The Big Red trailed 39-34 with 12:53 left but scored eight straight to take a three-point lead. Brown kept it close until Cornell pulled away. Tavon Blackmon had 14 points to lead Brown.
